    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-23T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-23T23:00:00-05:00" n="189"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.116/376: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-24T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1928—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received July 24—6:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>563. Following from Paxton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 23, 9 a.m. Yesterday evening I was informed that Gin-ling College
                            had been three times demanded as headquarters for Yen Hsi-shan during
                            the Fifth Plenary Conference.”<note n="84" xml:id="d189fn84">Fifth
                                plenary session of Central Executive Committee of the Kuomintang,
                                Nationalist Government.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
